50|$|Feedback-free {{instrumentation}} amplifier is {{the high}} input impedance differential amplifier designed without the external feedback network. This allows {{reduction in the number}} of amplifiers (one instead of three), reduced noise (no thermal noise is brought on by the feedback resistors) and increased bandwidth (no frequency compensation is needed). Chopper stabilized (or <b>zero</b> <b>drift)</b> instrumentation amplifiers such as the LTC2053 use a switching input front end to eliminate DC offset errors and drift.|$|E
